 Tools for UI/UX Design (Plain Text Format)
- Figma: A collaborative design and prototyping tool used for creating user interfaces and interactive mockups. Popular for team-based workflows and cloud access.
- Adobe XD: A vector-based tool for UI design and wireframing. It supports prototyping and integrates well with other Adobe products.
- Sketch: A Mac-exclusive design tool known for its simplicity and efficiency in creating UI components and layouts.
- InVision: Used for prototyping, sharing designs, and gathering feedback. It helps designers turn static screens into clickable experiences.
- Miro: A digital whiteboard tool ideal for mapping user journeys, brainstorming, and visual collaboration during UX research.
- Hotjar: A UX analytics tool that provides heatmaps, session recordings, and user feedback to understand how users interact with a product.

